Brent Crude Futures Premium to WTI Widens to $21.46 a Barrel

-- B y   R a c h e l   G r a h a m
-- 
2011-08-05T07:28:01Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-08-05/brent-crude-futures-premium-to-wti-widens-to-21-46-a-barrel.html
North Sea Brent crude futures’
premium to West Texas Intermediate, the U.S. benchmark, widened.  The difference between front-month Brent on ICE Futures
Europe Exchange and WTI on the  New York Mercantile Exchange  was
$21.46 a barrel at 8:09 a.m. London time, compared with $20.62 a
barrel at yesterday’s close,, according to data compiled by
Bloomberg. Brent’s premium closed at a record $22.67 on Aug. 2.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Rachel Graham in London at 
 rgraham13@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Stephen Voss at 
 sev@bloomberg.net  